A jewellery shop cashier suspected something was wrong and
acted. A group of suspects that was reportedly going to rob an NWJ jewellery
shop at Clearwater Mall, were disturbed by a cashier who suspected something
was not right and she pressed the panic button. The suspects then made a run for it speeding off, they then jumped
out into a house in Crutse street White City in Soweto, as cops had been
following them. One of the suspects was arrested, while three of the other
suspects managed to flee. Cops recovered one Glock gun a with filed off serial number. The suspect then pointed out a backyard room where they were
going to. The police went into the room and an AK47 was found in a bag
that the suspects were carrying when they got out of their getaway car. 